35 rogue of Quellious <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/upeon25.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Peon25</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://fenthen.hypermart.net/maeralin-littleicon.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(7/26/02 2:51:53 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=24490.topic&index=43>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: RE:</span><hr size=1> I read about half the Thott rant, and got tired of it. My opinion: stop whining. As the above poster stated, that I was going to say after reading the first line of whine, <b>Jack of all Trades, Master of None</a>.<br>
<br>
You want to compare Bards to Wizards, and then cry that they can't nuke as well? Give me a break. Can wizards melee? Can they run at super speed? Can they charm? No, stfu, thanks.<br>
<br>
Compare Bards to Rogues, shall we? Yeah, they can both dual wield, good job. But again, Rogues can't charm, run, heal, or have any mana regen capabilities. Rogues can't solo 3 mobs at once, for decent exp.<br>
<br>
Bards to Clerics! Oh my god, Bards can't heal as well! Let's have a pity party! Clerics have a worse damage-absorption rate than Bards, Rogues (chain), or Monks (leather). Even Shamen tank better than Clerics. Clerics can nuke better, thanks to the 925damage Luclin spell. But can we Mezz? Not without alot of rooting and stunning ;) Can we Charm? Nope.<br>
<br>
Stop crying, please. Bards get ALOT of skills, but end up short-ended on all of them by the end. In the begin game, Bards are on par with every other class, combined. They have the charm/mezz/mana of an Enchanter, Regen/Healing of Priests, Slows of a Shaman, and tank better than alot of other melee classes. If you want to play a Bard, you know damn well from the beginning that your usefulness gets cut short two-thirds of the way into your life. You're still a great class, fun to play as well, but just because you can do alot of things other classes can't, and classes that can do things you can end up doing it better, doesn't mean that you're broken. Necromancers are broken, not Bards. <p><center><a href="http://fenthen.hypermart.net" target=Fenthen><img src="http://fenthen.hypermart.net/FenJea1.gif" alt="Fenthen" border=0></A><br>
<a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=725" target="Fenthen">Fenthen Jus'taceio</a><br>
<a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=161965" target=Jeaza">Jeaza Belle</a></center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uzaspacer.showPublicProfile?language=EN>zaspacer</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(7/26/02 4:16:29 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=24490.topic&index=44>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Uh...</span><hr size=1> &quot;I've always disagreed with posting about other classes on a specific class board. Why? Because the board's class cannot give true insight into the issue at hand because they don't have a true understanding of the ins and outs of the other class.&quot;<br>
<br>
... I LOVE it because it gets discussion across classes going and helps people learn about other classes, or a class learn about what others feel about them. I love that this thread is still active.<br>
Thank you The Safehouse community, thank you posters )<br>
<br>
&quot;Bardic speed is a class-defining skill.&quot;<br>
<br>
... Bardic speed WAS a class-defining skill. Cleric exp rezzes were a class-defining skill.<br>
<br>
&quot;Bardic speed isn't a convenience. It does not solely exist to make travel easier. My speed is my survival. Allowing Horses into the game -does- equate into giving away Backstab or FD. Don't believe me?&quot;<br>
<br>
... I have to agree.<br>
Bard speed is one of the cornerstones of the solo bards game: we can't root, our snare takes 6 seconds to cast and last 18 seconds (IF not resisted), we cannot survive most exp mobs toe-to-toe melee.<br>
Bard speed, track, and invis are the cornerstones to bard outdoor pulling, CRs (with coprse song too of course), and scouting.<br>
<br>
&quot;You take away my speed? You nearly eliminate my ability to solo.&quot;<br>
<br>
... agree, but who said they are taking away your speed? Mobs can't buy horses... can they?<br>
I figure horses hurt PvP more.<br>
<br>
&quot;Any Bard worth their salt will never fess up to being a &quot;Jack of All Trades&quot;. Because we aren't.&quot;<br>
<br>
... agree, never quite understood that one. I always figured Druids were more of the &quot;Jack of All Trades&quot;.<br>
<br>
&quot;Running fast does not effect anything but travel and kiting. It was a nifty thing, but not much more than a parlor trick... similar to illusion masks, NOT backstab.&quot;<br>
<br>
... totally disagree. I think you'll find MANY classes will agree anything that is essential to their kiting is substantially more than &quot;a nifty thing/parlor trick&quot;.<br>
... even in raids or taking or uber encounters speed can be essential for pulling or kiting (to avoid despawn, to seive, etc.).<br>
<br>
&quot;everyone would play a bard&quot;<br>
<br>
... hehe, I would love to see more bards.<br>
Most people hate the labor involved with continual re-casting that also makes you unable to chat.<br>
<br>
&quot;BTW everyone who was crying about the horses bein ALMOSt as fast as their selos, are you forgetting that they cost like 30k&quot;<br>
<br>
... I'll pay 60k for FD/Backstab, is that cool? I'll even take one that takes a few seconds to activate, I'm not picky.<br>
<br>
&quot;bards get a much more convenient, cheaper (and 3% faster) song that they can whip out at any givin time&quot;<br>
<br>
... &quot;bardspeed&quot;:<br>
1) requires most bards to tie up both primary and secondary slots with a statless 2-handed item, making certain songs requiring other instruments (like their invis) practically impossible while traveling (until level 49 at which time we get a 2.5 minute duration speed song)<br>
2) lasts 18 seconds (until level 49) requiring constant recasting (taking up 1/3 of the 3 songs effects bards can have up at one time from constant recasting): I bought my bards TBoots which he used extensively until he was level 49.<br>
3) can miss notes on cast, and for some reason when a note is missed they usually  miss 1-5 times upon subsequent recasting attempts.<br>
4) does not allow for medding like horses do.<br>
<br>
&quot;You want to compare Bards to Wizards... Can they run at super speed?&quot;<br>
<br>
... they can now.<br>
<br>
&quot;Bards get ALOT of skills, but end up short-ended on all of them by the end.&quot;<br>
<br>
... my experience with my bard was that our playstyle and resources never scaled well. Consequently, our game evolves and changes to reflect new spells we get at different stages in our level advancement (as we ditch most the old ones that become worthless on mobs 5+ levels higher than the song). This really wasn't a problem for most levels as the new songs are GREAT as a bard advances.<br>
Until around 50, I did feel that bards were incredibly powerful.<br>
At 50+ most our old stuff breaks down comletely, and the new stuff we get is either unable to handle encounters at our level, or not enough be able to do more than MAYBE help another class get something done.<br>
Bard solo at high levels is all about using our 50- game on exp mobs from the 50- game.<br>
Bard group at high levels is all about helping enhance the real group you need to get the job done. The group doesn't need the bard, but maybe it can help speed em up. Conversely, if the group loses a key member (FD puller, Crowd Control, Tank, Healer, Damage, Slower, Rezzer) then it's over and everyone goes home.<br>
Old songs don't scale for bard (which in of itself is not a problem), and post 50, new songs are already inadequite to handle single group high level situations. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uryanflaw.showPublicProfile?language=EN>ryanflaw</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(7/27/02 4:49:06 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=24490.topic&index=45>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Uh...</span><hr size=1> Let's see, bards are very good soloers, very sought after and useful in exp groups, and very beneficial on raids.  Considering most classes can only claim one or two of those things, I really can't consider bards poor and neglected.  <br>
<br>
They have a couple of bugs?  AA isn't fantastic?  Some abilities don't work the way they prefer?  Well a lot of classes have issues like that, big deal.  Despite all that bards are still one of the overall strongest classes, period.  I simply cannot understand how Thott actually thinks bards are UNDERPOWERED! <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ukelyx.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kelyx</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://animatedgif.net/musicsound/musicnotes1_e0.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(7/29/02 10:01:46 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=24490.topic&index=46>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://animatedgif.net/musicsound/musicnotes1_e0.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: RE:</span><hr size=1> Bards need tweaking.  Nothing major.  Just some minor upgrades. <p><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=83551">Kelyx</a>
