<br>
What the heck is an XP group?<br>
Sounds like an oxymoron to me.<br>
Experience is best done for most (DEFINITELY not all) classes solo, or in an experience farming method like AoE groups.<br>
(NOTE: I WOULD DEFINITELY say that I think that ALL classes should be modified so they can have SOME form or soloing).<br>
Experience is one goal, and one that is most often best achieved doing repetitive motions in the same zone, on the same overcon mob... then moving to another overcon mob to do the same motions on when that mob light blues out.<br>
<br>
The real interesting stuff for me are the high level encounters/adventures that most often result in a LOSS of exp, but maybe camp/get a neat unique item or the chance to see a new zone/mob/etc.<br>
For these type things you need the classes that are gonna be able to handle situations: rez, heal, crowd control, tank, pull.<br>
<br>
I would like to see other non-bard classes changed so that they can enjoy some sort of real solo game (maybe make clerics able to solo certain undead mobs/encounters, etc.).<br>
<br>
I would like to see more dual class answers to basic needs of the group (like cleric/pal for rez); and done so that every class has a &quot;backup&quot; roll ability to at least one other, so many classes are already so close.<br>
<br>
On a side not, as a bard I think AoE songs hurts bards and should be removed.<br>
<br>
&quot;I have grouped with bards and I have never seen a better class when played correctly. Karnors WL room. 58 level bard was main tank, crowd control, healer, and puller. It was almost comical at the ease the bard had control of the room.&quot;<br>
<br>
Tank: bards can't tank.<br>
Maybe he was UBER equipped, maybe the mobs were trivial to his level.<br>
Crowd Control: bards can't use any of their crowd control on mobs 56+, making this great in EXP situations (farming weak mobs that still give exp) but insufficient in higher levels encounters.<br>
Healer: IF a 58 bard forgoes ALL melee (ok, they CAN use hand-to-hand... which maxxes at 100 and does virtually no damage) by equiping an UBER 2-handed 9 Agi, 9 Dex, 15 cha chunk of wood, AND dedicate 2 of the 3 songs they can have up at all times, THEN they can heal up to a staggering 37 hp's every 6 seconds.<br>
Puller: Bards can't FD, any bad pull in a dungeon and you run out of options quickly.<br>
Why is a 58 bard in Karnor's?<br>
<br>
&quot;I have seen bards kiting 20 mobs effectivly.&quot;<br>
<br>
Really?<br>
Bards can chant/fear kits one mob.<br>
Bards can quad kite with four mobs (1 pet and 3 mobs to beat on the pet).<br>
ANYTHING over 4 is just gonna aggro the bard and get in the way.<br>
Sure a bard can keep em on his tail to maybe more easily replace one of the 4 he is using to quad, but ultimately it is not mobs they are actually engaging.<br>
<br>
Bards CAN AoE TONS of mobs... as long as the mobs are low level green and are in one area. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uryandi.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ryandi</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(7/31/02 3:16:22 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=24490.topic&index=51>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Bard issues</span><hr size=1> &quot;Tank: bards can't tank.&quot; Can't tank raid mobs you mean? Cause any melee or hybrid can tank exp type mobs. Even high lvl exp mobs especially slowable ones.<br>
