Hinterdir, I am hoping with this thread to:<br>
1) expand non-bard general understanding of bards.<br>
2) expand bard general understanding from other classes.<br>
3) bounce ideas off non-bards and see if they make sense in a non-bard centric world.<br>
<br>
It affects the rogus class because it help that each class understand the other.<br>
Don't you find it helpful in play as a rogue to know the abilities/limits of what the classes you are grouped with can do?<br>
<br>
If this thread bugs the board I will move it, but there is so much valuable input lost when this type of thread is just referenced in a bard board.<br>
<br>
Now...<br>
<br>
&quot;Any melee or hybrid can tank exp type mobs. Even high lvl exp mobs especially slowable ones.&quot;<br>
<br>
Given a standard character from each class what is the order of tanking ability from greatest to least?<br>
(NOTE: I have NO clue, so PLEASE correct me where I am wrong)<br>
WAR &gt; PAL &gt; SHD &gt; RNG &gt; ROG &gt; SHM &gt; MNK &gt; BRD &gt; BST  CLR &gt; DRU &gt; WIZ &gt; ENC &gt; NEC &gt; MAG<br>
<br>
&quot;Since the introduction of aa means the exp grind never ends exp is still a valid area of the game 60 and beyond.&quot;<br>
<br>
Exp is like practice for the game.<br>
I agree that bards have an easy time at practice, they just aren't very impressive come game-time. (except for niche roles filled by 1 or 2 bards on raids)<br>
<br>
&quot;I think you can heal more than that while still meleeing with epic.&quot;<br>
<br>
If a level 58 bard equips epic to enhance the voice based heal component, juggles (swap out epic and lute with the casting of each voice/string based heal) Kelin's for the string based heal , and twist in the song amplification every 8th tick, then he/she can increase healing 4 more points to a total of 41 pts every 6 seconds.<br>
<br>
&quot;Also I've seen bards maintaining 5 songs at once meaning they could do 3 other things besides heal.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Special&quot; songs that can stack to produce more than 3 song sustained effects at once:<br>
<br>
* Amplification - increases voice based songs, lasts 30 seconds (drops if not cast every 8th song)<br>
* Song of Sustenance - freezes food consumption, lasts 1.5 minutes<br>
* Selo's Accelerating Chorus - bard speed, only works outdoors, lasts 2.5 minutes<br>
* Cinda's Charismatic Carillon - increase faction with one type, last until zone is left, self only, no icon<br>
* Breath of Harmony (bard only weapon, primary only) right insta-click - weapon must be equipped and does not stacked with bard healing songs<br>
* Song of Twilight - mez for level 55- mobs that lasts 5 ticks (2 more than normal)<br>
<br>
&quot;Btw that 37 hp a tick would represent 2220 dmg healed per minute indefinately spread out over 6 members. Thats more sustained healing than a 59 cleric can put out using the 59 heal over time.&quot;<br>
<br>
How many mobs are kind enough to spread damage over an entire party?<br>
Maybe in unique AoE only damage encounters.<br>
41 pts/tick would represent 410 dmg healed per minute.<br>
How many tanks take 410 damage per minute from a mob?<br>
I think ALL classes could tank at that dpm rate.<br>
(yes, dpm taken would be different for each class)<br>
<br>
&quot;In some exp grinds it should be the only healing you really need.&quot;<br>
<br>
Like fear kiting, quading, etc.? sure.<br>
Slaughtering massive amounts of overcons does not require tremendous defense or healing, I understand.<br>
<br>
&quot;Build a robust and skilled group and you should be able to handle overpulls in exp situations just don't bring the whole zone.&quot;<br>
<br>
In which case just about any class can pull.<br>
<br>
&quot;On the subject of kiting I have heard bards bragging about kiting far more than 4 mobs via the quading method described above. They called it swarm kiting.&quot;<br>
<br>
swarm kiting = (messy) quad kiting.<br>
When quad/swarm kiting, bards can only target 1 mob at a time, and only a max of 3 mobs will attack that mob when it is charmed (by the bard) and gains aggro (when it attacks another mob).<br>
All the other mobs will just be adds, ignoring the pet and chasing the bard.<br>
Bards use the 3 aggroed mobs to beat on their pet and get its hp very low, then when charm breaks the mobs damage is wiped, and a bard can get credit (exp) for chant kiting (running and DoTing) the now almost dead former pet.<br>
There are a max of 4 mobs involved at any one time.<br>
Sure, a bard can pull the entire zone, but they can only use 4 at a time. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/umalimuse.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Malimuse</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(8/1/02 9:23:06 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=24490.topic&index=54>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Bard issues</span><hr size=1> err....I have been soloing exp mobs in toe-to-toe melee since I was level 53, way before I got epic.  I have duo'd with rangers, warriors, monks, rogues, paladins, and shadowknights, and my regen (47th + 55th) is generally more than enough to keep up.  I have tanked mobs in the new CT, ssra, PoF, PoH, etc.....generally add mobs that can't be mezzed.  I have been in 6 person exp groups where the cleric nukes because our regen is just that good.  General exp mobs are cake for a bard to tank (VL, FG, Seb, the Grey, etc.), once they are slowed (even our piddely 31% slow at 60th).  I never chant kite, swarm kite, or charm kite (too boring for me).  I will occasionally fear kite in the Grey when waiting on raids to start.  Most of my solo exp is toe-to-toe melee, and I usually am surprised if I lose more than a half bubble of health.  And for reference, I am the 3rd or 4th best equipped bard in our guild (AoW, HP, Cursed, Tunare, etc capable guild).  There are a couple of bards outside our guild who have better stuff than I do.  I have roughly 3150 hps unbuffed and 1250 or so AC.....not even in the same zip code as Thott, Kinu, Bay, etc.<br>
<br>
As far as how effective we are on raids, anything more than 3-4 bards gets a bit much....but that can usually be said about shamans, enchanters, mages, Beastlords as well.  I am generally in the rogue group, because we have two bards that are farther along in AA points, and have Instrument Mastery etc., so one of them is generally in the main tank group.  With Damage shield stacking, our Main Tank gets a sustained 135 point DS.  In a fight against a mob like AoW (unslowable, flurries), that is basically like having 2 extra warriors hitting it for free.  In the rogue group, I add the 25% stackable haste, Rondo's (attack buff), and whatever utility song needs to be song (OOS, mana, whatever).  That means I am adding 12.5% free damage to every rogue in the group.....multiply that by 5, and there is about 3500 points/minute in damage just from the haste song.  I do roughly 3000 points/minute in melee myself (unless it is in Ssra, with the sick AC mobs) on raid mobs.  Other responsibilities that get split among the bards are Orb of Tishan (-33 to magic resistance), Journeyman's stick (-23 to magic resistance), and Claw of Zlandicar (AC, str, and agil debuff).  Because of our stacking, we can drop all of these on a mob (in addition to shaman/enchanter debuffs), meaning the mob is weaker and our raid force is stronger.  Having AoE mana means that only one bard has to sing it, and the other bards are free to do other things.  Saying that AoE mana song is bad for our class, basically says that you think bards are nothing more than mana whores. <br>
<br>
Not sure where you are getting that bards suck on raids, because we always want to have 3-4 bards on our raids.  I am not sure what you are raiding, where you are raiding, or what level you are, but a 60th level bard with IM3 and epic is a powerhouse.  I guess I must just be one of those lucky bards who is in a guild that has knowledge and respect for the class.  Don't generalize that &quot;all bards can't tank&quot;, &quot;raids don't want/need more than 1-2 bards&quot;, &quot;bards suck on raids&quot;, because at least in our guild that isn't even close to being true.  If you are going to make those statements, give the frame of reference you are working in.<br>
<br>
Mali <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uzaspacer.showPublicProfile?language=EN>zaspacer</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(8/1/02 11:18:49 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=24490.topic&index=55>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Bard issues</span><hr size=1> I apologize to the board for the bard v. bard nature of the post below.<br>
I don't want to run off non-bard readers by getting overly detailed in the semantics of bard play.<br>
<br>
Hopefully it will at least shed some more light for non-bards on the relative versatility of different bards at different levels.<br>
<br>
------------------------<br>
<br>
&quot;I have been soloing exp mobs in toe-to-toe melee since I was level 53&quot;<br>
&quot;I have tanked mobs in the new CT, ssra, PoF, PoH, etc.....generally add mobs that can't be mezzed.&quot;<br>
&quot;I have roughly 3150 hps unbuffed and 1250 or so AC&quot;<br>
&quot;I never chant kite, swarm kite, or charm kite (too boring for me).&quot;<br>
<br>
That is absolutely UBER UBER hp and armor and accomplishments.<br>
What the hell does your Magelo look like?<br>
3rd or 4th best? How insane are your guildmates equipped?<br>
<br>
In contrast, (while I am only level 54) I am considered VERY well equiped (&quot;twinked&quot;) with gear worth WELL over 100k+ and have maxed defense (for my level), and my stats are:<br>
1630 hp and 1049 AC unbuffed<br>
<br>
The feats you have been able to do, and the gear you have at your disposal are NOT indicative of the bard class for MOST people in the game.<br>
<br>
It's like tossing a Fungi on a lowbie and using that as a guideline to assess a classes abilities at the low end game.<br>
<br>
I have a level 26 Shammy with about 60k in gear and he can melee w/ no spells even cons without much difficulty, HOWEVER, this is NOT the rule for most Shamans at this level.<br>
<br>
&quot;Saying that AoE mana song is bad for our class, basically says that you think bards are nothing more than mana whores.&quot;<br>
<br>
AoE mana/resist songs reduce the need for multiple bards to fill those roles.<br>
As far as &quot;mana whores&quot;, there are times when a bard can be most effective for a group/raid by providing mana, but this is just one role that they can provide.<br>
<br>
&quot;Not sure where you are getting that bards suck on raids&quot;<br>
<br>
Bards do not suck on raids.<br>
I said &quot;bards... aren't very impressive come game-time. (except for niche roles filled by 1 or 2 bards on raids)&quot;<br>
How big are these raids using 3-4 bards?<br>
How many of them are needed on every raid?<br>
<br>
&quot;... not even in the same zip code as Thott, Kinu, Bay, etc.&quot;<br>
<br>
I really have not tried to address Thott's points directly in my posts, but I HOPE that Thott was addressing issues relative to the bard class in general, and NOT simply issues that he faces relative to his own game.<br>
<br>
That would be about as useful as Bill Gates asking the U.S. Treasury to print billion dollar bills so he can carry around cash easier.<br>
<br>
You are NOT playing a typical bard, nor do you play like a typical bard.<br>
For the record, we can take your post as confirmation that a an UBER equipped bard can play their own game.<br>
